    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4681750>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Ventral view of the hand of preserved topotypic specimens of Allobates trilineatus. (A) right hand of adult male (MHNSM 40420, SLV = 15.46 m), (B) left hand of adult female (MCP 14306, SVL = 15.78 mm). Insets: detailed views of outer lateral keels on Finger I." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4681750/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4681752>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Ventral view of right foot of preserved topotypic specimens of Allobates trilineatus. (A) adult male (MHNMS 40420, SVL = 15.46 mm). (B) adult female (MCP 14306, SVL = 15.78 mm). Orange arrow points to the metatarsal fold. White rectangles delimit magnified regions illustrating detailed views of lateral keels." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4681752/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4663877>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Dorsolateral and ventral views of topotypic live specimens of Allobates trilineatus. An adult male (MCP 14309, SVL= 15.9 mm) with the pale vertebral line on dorsum illustrated in the holotype and a densely pigmented throat (A, B). An adult male (MCP 14307, SVL= 15.8 mm) lacking the pale vertebral line and with lighter ventral coloration (C, D). An adult female (MCP 14306, SVL= 15.8 mm), note the absence of melanophores in ventral surfaces (E, F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4663877/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4663879>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Color pattern variation in Allobates trilineatus illustrated by some topotypic specimens. (A) Dorsolateral view of an adult female (MCP 14317, SVL= 14.6 mm); note conspicuous pale oblique lateral stripe extending from groin to middle body. (B) Dorsal view of an adult male (MCP 14304, SVL= 15.0 mm); note comma-shaped, light yellow paracloacal marks. Dorsolateral (C) and ventral (D) views of a juvenile specimen (MCP 14302, SVL= 10.8 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4663879/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4663881>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Dorsal color pattern variation of preserved topotypic adult males of Allobates trilineatus. (A) and (B) specimens with a distinct and diffuse pale vertebral line (MCP 14309 and MCP 14304, respectively). (C) Dorsolateral stripe merging with lighter color of the urostyle region, dorsum with dark irregular spots on lighter background (MCP 14316). (D) Specimen with three transversal dark brown blotches on shank (MNHSM 40420). (E) Specimen lacking transversal dark brown blotches on shank (MHNSM 40421)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4663881/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4663883>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. (A–D) Dorsal color pattern variation of topotypic preserved females (A–D) and unsexed juveniles (E–F) of Allobates trilineatus. (A), (B) and (C) Specimens with uniform dark brown on dorsum (MCP 14306, MHNSM 40423 and MCP 14311 respectively). (D) Specimen with dark irregular spots on lighter background on dorsum (MCP 14317). (E) and (F) Juvenile specimens (MHNSM 40422 and MCP 14313, respectively)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4663883/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4681756>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Lateral color pattern variation of preserved topotypic specimens of Allobates trilineatus. (A), (B) and (C) Adult males (MCP 14309, MHNSM 40421, and 40420, respectively). (D), (E) and (F) Adult females (MCP 14306, 14311 and 14317, respectively). (G) and (H) Juveniles (MHNSM 40422 and MCP 14313, respectively)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4681756/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4663887>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Ventral color pattern variation of preserved topotypic male specimens of Allobates trilineatus. (A) MCP 14309, (B) MCP 14304, (C) MCP 14316, (D) MHNSM 40420, (E) MHNSM 40421." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4663887/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4663889>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Ventral color pattern variation of preserved topotypic adult females (A–D) and unsexed juveniles (E–F) of Allobates trilineatus. (A) MCP 14306, (B) MHNSM 40423, (C) MCP 14311, (D) MCP 14317, (E) MHNSM 40422,, (F) MCP 14313." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4663889/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4663891>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Waveform (upper graph) and spectrogram (lower graph) of the advertisement call of a topotypic male of Allobates trilineatus (MCP 14312, SVL = 15.46 mm) recorded in Munichis, Yurimaguas, Loreto, Peru, in February 2019. Air temperature at time of recording was 26.7 °C." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4663891/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4663893>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Phylogenetic relationships of Allobates (log likelihood = -8552.38) inferred from a maximum likelihood analysis of 605 bp of the mitochondrial gene 16S and considering indels as missing data. Numbers on branches are bootstrap frequencies (percentage) of 1000 pseudoreplicates. Only bootstrap values above 50 are shown. The taxonomy proposed in this work is indicated in the tree." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4663893/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4663869>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Map of western Amazonia with symbols indicating the known geographic records of Allobates trilineatus. Brown shade illustrates the distribution of the species according to Icochea et al. (2004). Star: A. trilineatus type locality in Yurimaguas, Loreto, Peru. Brown circles: geographic records based on Grant & Rodriguez (2001), with additions and updates by Morales (2002), Melo-Sampaio et al. (2018), and Réjaud et al. (2020). White-ringed circles: localities with DNA sequences available from public repositories, all included in our phylogenetic analysis. Green circle: locality of a new species identified in this study through DNA sequences, but previously assigned to A. trilineatus by Grant & Rodriguez (2001) based on external morphology." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4663869/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

